  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed. The assessment team concluded Medium assurance is supported by the breadth of multi-lab experimental coverage, the conservative acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96), and the independent code-verification activities. One factor (Test conditions) achieved below its required level owing to single-load-configuration testing; however, the team judged this shortfall to be offset by the robustness of the remaining 12 factors and the supplementary sensitivity analysis demonstrating negligible load-angle sensitivity.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
